    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-05T06:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-05T06:35:00-05:00" n="168"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1900: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-05T15:00:00+03:25"
                            >August 5, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 5—12:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>250. My 248, August 2.<note n="40" xml:id="d168fn40">Not printed.</note>
                        Qavam<note n="41" xml:id="d168fn41">Ahmad Qavam.</note> has assumed duties
                    as Prime Minister and is actively engaged in forming Cabinet which he expects to
                    present to Majlis next Sunday. United Press and Associated Press representatives
                    in interview with Qavam yesterday were much impressed with evident warmth of his
                    statements that he desires strengthen relations with the United States and to
                    obtain American advisers. He spoke of things American to exclusion other topics.
                    When asked what his program would be Qavam picked up a piece of bread from his
                    desk and replied “This is my program, if I can put bread of good quality in
                    hands of all Iranians other problems will be easy to solve”. There are
                    indications Qavam will form relatively strong Cabinet and that he intends to
                    deal with Iran’s pressing food, transport, security and other internal problems
                    with dispatch and energy. I see no reason to believe he will fail to cooperate
                    with Allies. Perhaps to test him on this point British Minister is seeing him
                    today to insist on arrest of a number of persons suspected of pro-German
                    activities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
